			<content>[blad 1] Jan Brueghel, Influence of P.B.I. Hanover Landscape signed dan dated : J. Brueghel 1603 (Katalog der Kunstsammlung im Provinzial Museum zu Hannover, Bd I, Gemälde, Handzeichnungen und Aquarelle, Berlin 1930, N° 19 (p. 121), copper, 19,7 x 25,7. Clearly under influence of Darmstadt picture: Relation of foreground to background- rocky mountain motifs etc.; 
[vouwbladen nrs 2 -3] Alexander DORNER, Das älteste Bild des Sammetbrueghel, in: Jahrbuch des Provinzial Museum Hannover 1926, pp. 44-48, citaten pp. 44, n.45, p. 46; 
[blad 4] Jan Brueghel Atti di Donazioni del Cardinale Federico Borromeo alla Biblioteca Ambrosiana, 28 aprile 1618, reprinted in Guidi Sommario dello Bibliotheca Ambrosiana Milano 1907, pp. 132-140 here Brueghel pp. 135ff.; 
[blad 5, 6, 7, 8] Mgr. Maurice VAES, Le Journal de Jean Brueghel II, Bulletin de l'Institut historique belge de Rome, VI, 1926, pp. 163-222, citaten 170, 171, 172, 173, 177, 178, 181, 182, 194, 195; 
[blad 9, met nummer 1, recto-verso] Jan B. Literature: Oldenbourg, Katalog der St. Lukas, ?,1935; Joseph Alexander Graf Raczynski, Die flämische Landschaft vor Rubens, pp. 53-55; 
[blad 10, met nummer 2, recto-verso] Raczynski, citaten pp. 53, 54; 
[blad 11] Jan Brueghel, BM. Fenwick, p. 179, n° 2 (Pieter BRVEGEL) now in Printroom as Jan B I Canal with boats, orthogonal 1946-7-13-148, actually very near to P.B.I, pure pen. Another Fenwick drawing (p. 178) 1946-7-13-146 signed Joan breugel in Neurembeurg, wooded landscape 1617 (corse ? for 1616) brown pen, blue wash; Attributed to J.B.; Hind, Catalogue, Rubens, Flemish Artists XV, p. 96N° 16: Woman with basket, on head=ex. copy from 'Heath'; 
[blad 12, rect-verso] J. Denucé, Letters and Documents concerning Jan Bruegel I and II, Antwerp 1934, citaten pp. 7, 8; 
[blad 13] Musée National du Louvre, Catalogue Raisonné des Peintures du Moyen-Âge de la Renaissance..., Peintures Flamande du XV et XVI S., Ed. Michel 1953, Jan BRVEGHEL I, Giov. CRIVELLI; de Boer, Exh. 1934; DENUCÉ, Jan, Letters & Documents concerning Jan Brueghel I and II, Antwerp 1934, One of series: Historical Sources for the Study of Flemish Art; COMBE, Jacques, Brueghel de Velours, Paris 1943, One of series: Chefs d' oeuvre de l' art flamand; CLERICI, Fabrizio, Allegorie dei sensi di Jan Brueghel, Firenze, 1946; Raczynski; Thiéry; ?; Paris Exhibition Rubens catal. by [onleesbaar]; Bergström, Still-Life; 
[blad 14, 15, 16, 17 met nummers 1 t/m 4] Jan Brueghel, Ed. Michel, Louvre cat. 1953, citaten pp. 43f, 44, 47, 48, 50, 52; 
[7 ingevulde bibliotheekformulieren Victoria & Albert Museum].</content>
